fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Let A be a complete local Noetherian ring, with residue field k, and let \mathfrak {X} be a proper formal scheme over A (endowed with its \mathfrak {r}(A)-adic topology). We suppose that
the local rings of \mathcal {O}_{\mathfrak {X}} are flat A-modules, or, equivalently, that, if we endow \mathcal {O}_{\mathfrak {X}} and A with the filtration given by powers of the maximal ideal of A, then the associated graded algebras satisfy \operatorname {gr}(\mathcal {O}_{\mathfrak {X}}) \simeq \operatorname {gr}^0(\mathcal {O}_{\mathfrak {X}})\otimes _k\operatorname {gr}(A);
\operatorname {H}^2(\mathfrak {X}_0,\mathcal {O}_{\mathfrak {X}_0})=0, where we consider \mathfrak {X}_0=\mathfrak {X}\otimes _Ak as an algebraic scheme over k;
\mathfrak {X}_0 is projective.
Then, under these conditions, \mathfrak {X} is algebraisable, and, more precisely, is isomorphic to \overline {X}, where X is some projective A-scheme.

